717778f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 184th Street (West)
717778f-a.text:
Broadway, north from Nest 184th Street, showing an old house at
186th Street and St. Elizabeths Church (E. C.) at 1S7th Street.
On the ridge are the Sweetser, Witherspoon and Barna)d plSces.
These are seen also in view E.
E. P. Chrystie  Karch 11, 1923

717779f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 184th Street
717779f-a.text:
(1)
4320-4324 Broadway, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of
184th Street. The two centre buildings are three-story frame
houses.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection Wuseum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 65.
CREDIT LINE IMMERTIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same view from a slightly different angle. Note frame house
at the rear of No. 4322, adjoining the N.E. corner.
November 3, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
Another view of the afore mentioned corner, and also including
a further view northward.

NO REPRODUCTIONS.
